mainBoard.flavorText:
1.
One day, night will come to these mountains.
mainBoard.name: Mountain

mainBoard.flavorText:
2.
Our days of idle pleasure winnow down; their sweetness doubles as their numbers dwindle.
mainBoard.name: Mountain

mainBoard.flavorText:
3.
The day draws back, the time of struggle ebbs. Sun-scarred relics lie about the land.
mainBoard.name: Mountain

mainBoard.flavorText:
4.
Here and there an oracle who sees the night ahead: the rude glimmer of it, tucked into the corners of our sky.
mainBoard.name: Mountain

mainBoard.flavorText:
5.
Here, in the winding labyrinth, no shelter;
mainBoard.name: Mountain

mainBoard.flavorText:
6.
Here, beneath an ancient throne, small comfort.
mainBoard.name: Mountain

mainBoard.flavorText:
7.
Into the dust of the road, the dusk must burrow. From crag to creekside and past all points beyond, the evening falls.
mainBoard.name: Mountain

mainBoard.flavorText:
8.
Night gathers where the flamekin wail, its fingers at their throats. Our compact with the darkness was for nothing.
mainBoard.name: Mountain

mainBoard.flavorText:
9.
One day, the day will find its furthest limit, the place beyond which no days are imagined: a place long sealed away, lost within the endless mountain range. One day, the night will find this place, and breach it.
mainBoard.name: Mountain

mainBoard.flavorText:
10.
On that day, then, the night will come to Lorwyn.
—Narvek Riag, kithkin prophet
mainBoard.name: Mountain
